title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester Model 24, 12 Ga, 30" barrels, 1951 Mfg
postcontent:
I have a good, solid Model 24 that I no longer need.
It was made in 1951, based on the serial number.
The gun is in good shape, considering it's age. The stock is Black Walnut, very solid with no cracks or repairs.
The butt plate appears to be original and is undamaged.
My gunsmith estimated the barrel finish at ~80%, the receiver finish closer to 90%, and the overall gun about 85%.
Look around on other sites and compare the condition and price of this Model 24 against the others. You'll see that this is a really nice deal.
There is no real damage anywhere, just typical little dings and wear that you'd expect to see on a 50-yr old gun.
When I received it, the right chamber was unsafe to load, as it would often fire when closed.
I disassembled the action and discovered that the right side firing pin and sear were both very worn. It appears that the original owner liked shooting the modified side more than the full side! :)
I purchased and installed a new sear and right side firing pin. The gun now performs flawlessly and is once again safe to shoot.
This will make someone a fine bird gun.
I'm posting some photos, but please feel free to email me if you want to see anything specific.

Here's a link to an Imageshack album with a few more photos: http://img830.imageshack.us/g/stockclose.jpg/

Armslist doesn't allow html in posts, so you'll have to cut and paste the link, sorry!

We have black receivers in stock and ready to ship. Cavalry Arms is no longer making these lowers, so get one before they're gone!

CUSTOM ENGRAVING IS AVAILABLE FOR ALL PURCHASERS!

For just $25 we will custom engrave your lower so that in the future you can register it on an ATF Form 1 as a short-barrelled rifle.

We are happy to ship to CA and these are legal with a bullet button. We do not charge extra for CC's. We wait two weeks for personal checks to clear before shipping to your FFL. All sales final. Please visit us online at EFI, LLC and check out our custom rifle builds!

For the folks unfamiliar with a Cavalry Arms lower:

These receivers are injection molded from glass filled nylon 6, a polymer material very similar to that used by other firearms companies. Polymer offers unsurpassed corrosion resistance, finish durability. and is significantly lighter than aluminum based receivers.

They are molded in two halves and assembled using a linear vibration welding process. Linear vibration welding forms the two halves into one solid piece. Every contact surface between the two halves is bonded together with a weld that is even stronger than the parent material.

Injection molding allows for more cost effective and faster production of parts of consistent quality. Production cost savings are passed onto the consumer.

CAV-15 MKII Receiver Features:

    * A1 Length integral Stock (5/8" shorter than A2) with sling loop. 13" Length of Pull.
    * Ergonomically enhanced integral pistol grip
    * Wider magazine well capable of accepting .45 Greasegun magazines with caliber conversion upper receivers and magazine blocks.
    * Standard AR15 magazines can be used without modifications.
    * Receiver weight (complete) is 1 full pound lighter than complete aluminum receiver with A2 stock
    * Uses all standard mil-spec parts with the exception of the take down pins. The front pivot and rear pins are a Quick Take down style with Detents built into them, allowing for quick and easy removal of the pins while maintaining a positive lock.

Gunsmithing

Let EFI, LLC's experienced gunsmith keep your firearms in top working order! Our specialties include Sig Sauer Pistols, AR15/M16 Series, UZI, 1911 Pistols, Remington Rifles, and HK 90-Series. Engraving

Whether you need a quick turn-around for engraving your receiver for a short-barreled rifle, or you would like a custom graphic on your gun, EFI, LLC can meet that need. Price will vary based on number of characters or complexity of graphic.

Parkerizing

EFI, LLC will take your firearm, disassemble it, inspect all parts for wear and advise you if any should be replaced to keep your firearm in good working order. We will then remove the current finish and any contaminants, and prepare the surface using a grit blast method that allows for a stronger finish to be applied. After the parkerization process is complete, we will again inspect, clean, lubricate, and reassemble your firearm. Both zinc and manganese parkerizing are available.

Consignments

The GSG-5 also utilizes the H&K style drum sight, which can be adjusted for both windage and elevation.
